{{nihongo|'''''Kamen Rider W'''''|仮面ライダーＷ（ダブル）|Kamen Raidā Daburu|also called '''''Kamen Rider Double'''''}} is a 2009-2010 Japanese [[tokusatsu]] drama, the eleventh series in the [[Heisei period]] run of the [[Kamen Rider Series]]. It premiered following the finale of ''[[Kamen Rider Decade]]'' on September 6, 2009,<ref>''Uchuusen'' No. 125</ref> and aired alongside ''[[Samurai Sentai Shinkenger]]'' in [[TV Asahi]]'s [[Super Hero Time]] programming block. Following ''Shinkenger's'' finale, it aired alongside ''[[Tensou Sentai Goseiger]]'', until ''W'' concluded on August 29, 2010. The series is described as the {{nihongo4|"Heisei Kamen Rider 10th Anniversary Project: Fall Campaign"|平成仮面ライダー10周年プロジェクト 秋の陣|Heisei Kamen Raidā Jusshūnen Purojekuto: Aki no Jin}}. In the first episode of Kamen Rider Fourze, W is revealed to be in the same [[Continuity (fiction)|continuity]] as the original Showa timeline, making it the first series to do so since ''[[Kamen Rider Agito]]''.<ref>[[Kamen Rider Fourze]], Episode 1: Youthful Transformation, Aired September 4, 2011</ref>

==Promotion==
Advertisements throughout the months of May, June, and July 2009 built up to the debut of Kamen Rider W,<ref name="tvkun809"/> who first appeared at the 10th Anniversary Project MASKED RIDER LIVE & SHOW event,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tv-asahi.co.jp/decade/liveshow/index.html|title=10th Anniversary ProjectMASKED RIDER LIVE & SHOW～十年祭～｜テレビ朝日｜仮面ライダーディケイド|accessdate=2009-06-10}}</ref> and also featured in ''[[Kamen Rider Decade: All Riders vs. Dai-Shocker]]''.

[[Hiroshi Tanahashi]] of [[New Japan Pro Wrestling]] is a self-admitted fan of ''Kamen Rider W'', and in June 2010 made a new costume designed after Kamen Rider Double FangJoker's design<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.njpw.co.jp/news/article.php?nwid=12182|title=2010年06月25日 {{!}} 棚橋選手が雑誌『De☆View 8月号』に登場！ なんと"若菜姫"こと飛鳥凛さんに"筋力トレーニング"をレクチャー!! {{!}} 新日本プロレスオフィシャルWEBサイト　-NEWS-|date=June 25, 2010|accessdate=2010-06-28}}</ref> and wore it to a match in [[Osaka]] on June 19.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.njpw.co.jp/result/index.php?COM=result_disp&SRNO=159&TKNO=1&MTCH_NUM=8&CRS_NO=0|title=新日本プロレスオフィシャルWEBサイト　-試合結果-|accessdate=2010-06-28}}</ref> [[Rin Asuka]] also appeared at the match to promote the show.

==Production and casting==
[[File:Tokyo National Museum, Honkan 2010.jpg|thumb|left|The [[Tokyo National Museum]]'s ''Honkan'' building is used as the facade for the lavish mansion of the Sonozaki family.]]

The series' main writer is [[Riku Sanjo]] and the main director is [[Ryuta Tasaki]]. The theme song titled "[[W-B-X (W-Boiled Extreme)|W-B-X ~W-Boiled Extreme~]]" is performed by [[Aya Kamiki]] with former [[Judy and Mary|JUDY AND MARY]] guitarist [[Takuya (singer)|TAKUYA]] as the unit {{nihongo4|"Aya Kamiki w TAKUYA"|上木彩矢 w TAKUYA|Kamiki Aya wizu TAKUYA}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nikkansports.com/entertainment/news/f-et-tp0-20090629-512230.html|title=桐山漣と菅田将暉が合体で仮面ライダーＷ - 芸能ニュース : nikkansports.com|accessdate=2009-06-29}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.walkerplus.com/2009/0629/15/|title=新イケメンライダーはジャニーズ系美男子でW主演！ - 東京ウォーカー|accessdate=2009-06-29}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://contents.oricon.co.jp/news/movie/67270/full/|title=新・仮面ライダーは"2人で1人"の「仮面ライダーW」 ニュース-ORICON STYLE-|accessdate=2009-06-29|date=2009-06-29}}</ref> The creature designer is [[Katsuya Terada]], previously the character designer for ''[[Blood: The Last Vampire]]'', the designer of [[Monster X]] for ''[[Godzilla: Final Wars]]'', the designer of Cutie Honey's costume for ''[[Cutie Honey (film)|Cutie Honey]]'', and the mechanic and character design refinement for ''[[Yatterman (film)|Yatterman]]''.

Newcomer [[Masaki Suda]] portrays the mysterious Philip. Drama actor [[Renn Kiriyama]], who made his acting debut as Bunta Marui in [[Tenimyu#Absolute King Rikkai feat. Rokkaku ~ First Service|''Musical Prince of Tennis: Absolute King Rikkai feat. Rokkaku ~ First Service'']], joins the cast as Shotaro Hidari. [[Hikaru Yamamoto]], who made her acting debut in ''[[Watashitachi no Kyōkasho]]'' as Chiharu Nobue, portrays the female lead Akiko Narumi. Comedian and actor [[Takeshi Nadagi]] portrays Mikio Jinno and veteran actor [[Minori Terada]], known for his leading role in ''[[The Human Bullet]]'', portrays Ryubee Sonozaki.

==Story==
{{main|List of Kamen Rider W characters}}
Many people live in peace and harmony in {{nihongo4|Futo|風都|Fūto|the "[[Windy City (disambiguation)|Windy City]]"}}, an ecologically-minded and [[windmill|wind-powered]] city. However, this peace is undermined by the [[List of Kamen Rider W characters#Sonozaki Family|Sonozaki Family]], who sell mysterious [[USB flash drive|flash drive]]-like devices called [[Gaia (mythology)|Gaia]] Memories to criminals and other interested parties. These individuals use the Gaia Memories to become [[Dopant (Kamen Rider)|Dopants]], committing crimes with the police force powerless to stop them. To make matters worse, the Gaia Memories can cause their users to go insane, to the point where they could die from using the devices unrestrained. After the death of his [[Kamen Rider Skull|boss]], the self-proclaimed hard-boiled (actually half-boiled) detective Shotaro Hidari works with the mysterious Philip, who possesses a set of purified Gaia Memories, to investigate Dopant-related crimes in Futo. With their Gaia Memories and the Double Driver belts, Shotaro and Philip transform and combine into [[Kamen Rider Double (character)|Kamen Rider Double]] to fight the Dopant menace and keep Futo safe. While joined in their fight by investigator Ryu Terui, who transforms into [[Kamen Rider Accel]], the mystery of Philip's past, his relation to the Sonozaki Family, and their Museum organization are revealed.<ref name="tvkun809">''Telebikun'' August 2009</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.toei.co.jp/tv/w/story/1189003_1613.html|title=仮面ライダーダブル introduction｜東映［テレビ］| accessdate=2009-06-30}}</ref>

==Episodes==
{{main|List of Kamen Rider W episodes}}
All episodes of ''Kamen Rider W'' have two titles: the first indicates a story arc while the second indicates the episode's title. The letter of the [[Latin alphabet]] in the story arc title has a [[double meaning]]: it represents a major character (Kamen Rider, Dopant, or otherwise) that is featured in the arc and another English word that indicates the theme of the arc.

{{:List of Kamen Rider W episodes}}

==Wind Wave Internet radio==
To tie into the show, TV Asahi, Toei, and [[Avex Trax]] have produced the Wind Wave FM [[Internet radio]] station. Only one of the shows, {{nihongo4|''Wakana's Healing Princess''|園咲若菜のヒーリングプリンセス|Sonozaki Wakana no Hīringu Purinsesu}}, also exists within the fiction of ''Kamen Rider W''. The other programs, DJ Hurry Kenn's ''FU-TO Hit on Groove'' music show and [[Tsuyoshi Himura|Tsuyoshi]] and [[Mitsuhiro Ayano|Ayano]]'s {{Nihongo4|''Head Wind: One-Game Match!!''|向い風 一本勝負!!|Mukaikaze Ipponshōbu!!}} show, treat the television series as fiction, explicitly referring to the songs they play as theme songs (as part of a mail in request, DJ Hurry Kenn played [[AAA (band)|AAA DEN-O form]]'s "[[Climax Jump]]", and referred to it as the theme song for ''[[Kamen Rider Den-O]]''). All of ''Double''{{'}}s theme songs have been played as part of the various radio shows, several of which were first heard on the "radio" before being utilized as part of an episode's soundtrack. On March 7, a new radio show featuring [[Queen & Elizabeth]] titled {{nihongo4|''Queen & Elizabeth's White Hearts!!''|QueenとElizabethの白抜きハートマーク!!|Kuīn to Erisabesu no Shironuki Hātomāku!!}} began "airing", but was discontinued a month later. To mirror the current events in the show's story, ''Healing Princess'' was cancelled on June 13, 2010.

==Films==

===''All Riders vs. Dai-Shocker''===
{{main|Kamen Rider Decade: All Riders vs. Dai-Shocker}}
[[Kamen Rider Double (character)|Kamen Rider Double]], voiced by Kiriyama and Suda, made his debut appearance in ''[[Kamen Rider Decade]]''{{'}}s first film ''[[Kamen Rider Decade: All Riders vs. Dai-Shocker]]''. During the movie, Double arrive to fight Shadow Moon, before heading back to Futo.

===''Movie War 2010''===
{{main|Kamen Rider × Kamen Rider W & Decade: Movie War 2010}}
As part of the {{nihongo4|''Kamen Rider × Kamen Rider W & Decade: Movie War 2010''|仮面ライダー×仮面ライダー Ｗ（ダブル）&ディケイド MOVIE大戦2010|Kamen Raidā × Kamen Raidā Daburu Ando Dikeido Mūbī Taisen Nisenjū}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.toei.co.jp/movie/details/1189805_951.html|title=仮面ライダー×仮面ライダー　W＆ディケイドMOVIE大戦２０１０ {{!}} 東映［映画］|accessdate=2009-10-03}}</ref> triple feature, ''W''{{'}}s film {{nihongo4|''Kamen Rider W: Begins Night''|劇場版　仮面ライダーＷ（ダブル）～ビギンズナイト～|Kamen Raidā Daburu ~Biginzu Naito~}} opened in Japanese theaters on December 12, 2009. The film expands on the origins of Kamen Rider W, featuring guest star [[Koji Kikkawa]] as Shotaro's mentor and Akiko's father Sokichi Narumi.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sponichi.co.jp/entertainment/news/2009/10/05/02.html |title=吉川晃司が変身！前代未聞のドクロライダー（芸能） ― スポニチ Sponichi Annex ニュース |accessdate=2009-10-05 |date=2009-10-05 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091006025546/http://www.sponichi.co.jp/entertainment/news/2009/10/05/02.html |archivedate=2009-10-06 |df= }}</ref> The events of the movie take place between episodes 14 and 15.

===''A to Z/The Gaia Memories of Fate''===
{{main|Kamen Rider W Forever: A to Z/The Gaia Memories of Fate}}
In addition to the ''Movie War 2010'' films, ''Double'' also has a feature film titled {{nihongo4|''Kamen Rider W Forever: A to Z/The Gaia Memories of Fate''|仮面ライダーＷ（ダブル） FOREVER AtoZ／運命のガイアメモリ|Kamen Raidā Daburu Fōebā Ē tu Zetto/Unmei no Gaia Memori}}. Filmed in [[3-D film|3-D]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://japanimate.com/Entry/1480/|title=「アバター」に続け、国産３Ｄ映画への挑戦、ノウハウ手探り－アニメニュース Japanimate.com|date=2010-04-24|accessdate=2010-04-24}}</ref> it was released in theaters on August 7, 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.toei.co.jp/movie/details/1191401_951.html|title=劇場版 仮面ライダーW／天装戦隊ゴセイジャー THE MOVIE {{!}} 東映［映画］|accessdate=2010-05-05}}</ref> [[Mitsuru Matsuoka]], lead singer of [[Sophia (Japanese band)|Sophia]] serves as the film's primary antagonist. It also features the first on-screen appearance of the 12th Heisei Kamen Rider: [[Kamen Rider OOO (character)|Kamen Rider OOO]]. The events of the movie take place between episodes 44 and 45.

===''Movie War Core''===
{{main|Kamen Rider × Kamen Rider OOO & W Featuring Skull: Movie War Core}}
The second Movie War film to primarily feature W, titled {{nihongo4|''Kamen Rider × Kamen Rider OOO & W Featuring Skull: Movie War Core''|仮面ライダー×仮面ライダー オーズ&ダブル feat.スカル MOVIE大戦CORE|Kamen Raidā × Kamen Raidā Ōzu Ando Daburu Fīcharingu Sukaru Mūbī Taisen Koa}}, was released in theatres on December 18, 2010, with the main ''W'' section titled {{nihongo4|''Kamen Rider Skull: Message for Double''|仮面ライダースカル メッセージforダブル|Kamen Raidā Sukaru: Messēji fō Daburu}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cinema-ginsei.com/maeuri.html|title=CINEMA GINSEI /シネマハーヴェストウォーク|date=September 5, 2010|accessdate=September 5, 2010}}</ref>

===''Let's Go Kamen Riders''===
{{main|OOO, Den-O, All Riders: Let's Go Kamen Riders}}
Kiriyama and Suda made a cameo appearance, reprising their roles as Shotaro Hidari and Philip in the 40th anniversary film {{nihongo4|''OOO, Den-O, All Riders: Let's Go Kamen Riders''|オーズ・電王・オールライダー レッツゴー仮面ライダー|Ōzu Den'ō Ōru Raidā Rettsu Gō Kamen Raidā}}.

===''Movie War Mega Max''===
{{main|Kamen Rider × Kamen Rider Fourze & OOO: Movie War Mega Max}}
Kiriyama and Suda reprise their roles as Shotaro Hidari and Philip in the 2011 film {{nihongo4|''Kamen Rider × Kamen Rider Fourze & OOO: Movie War Mega Max''|仮面ライダー×仮面ライダー フォーゼ&オーズ MOVIE大戦MEGA MAX|Kamen Raidā × Kamen Raidā Fōze Ando Ōzu Mūbī Taisen Mega Makkusu}}, released on December 10, 2011. The third out of the 5 parts of this Movie War, {{nihongo4|''Futo: The Conspiracy Advances''|風都 暗躍する陰謀|Fūto Anyaku Suru Inbō}}, takes places in Futo and features Kamen Rider Double continuing his battle against Foundation X.

===''Kamen Rider Taisen''===
{{main|Heisei Rider vs. Shōwa Rider: Kamen Rider Taisen feat. Super Sentai}}
{{nihongo4|''Heisei Rider vs. Shōwa Rider: Kamen Rider Taisen feat. Super Sentai''|平成ライダー対昭和ライダー 仮面ライダー大戦 feat.スーパー戦隊|Heisei Raidā Tai Shōwa Raidā Kamen Raidā Taisen Fīcharingu Sūpā Sentai}} made its theater debut on March 29, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.superhero-movie.com/ |title=平成ライダー対昭和ライダー 仮面ライダー大戦 feat.スーパー戦隊（仮） |publisher=Superhero-movie.com |date= |accessdate=2013-12-14}}</ref> [[Masahiro Inoue]], playing ''[[Kamen Rider Decade]]'', alongside many other lead actors of other series appear in the film, including [[Gaku Sano]] of ''[[Kamen Rider Gaim]]'', [[Renn Kiriyama]] of ''Kamen Rider W'', [[Kohei Murakami]] and [[Kento Handa]] of ''[[Kamen Rider 555]]'', [[Shunya Shiraishi]] from ''[[Kamen Rider Wizard]]'', [[Ryo Hayami]] of ''[[Kamen Rider X]]'',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ustream.tv/recorded/42594148 |title=新春白金キャンパスアーティストファイ部犯罪被害者支援チャリティ音楽祭。, Recorded on 2014/01/10今年初の白金キャンパスアーティストファイ部。1月4日の東京芸術劇場のチャリティ支援音楽祭は超素晴らしかった、涙出たよ！そして今月19日に行われる、みえ犯罪被害者総合支援センターの「犯罪被害者支 |publisher=Ustream.tv |date= |accessdate=2014-01-19 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140116104324/http://www.ustream.tv/recorded/42594148 |archivedate=2014-01-16 |df= }}</ref> and [[Hiroshi Fujioka]] of the original ''[[Kamen Rider]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cinematoday.jp/page/N0059718 |title=藤岡弘、38年ぶりに仮面ライダー1号に変身！ - シネマトゥデイ |publisher=Cinematoday.jp |date=2014-01-17 |accessdate=2014-01-17}}</ref> The Sentai teams' ''[[Ressha Sentai ToQger]]'' and [[Ryo Ryusei]] as Daigo Kiryu from ''[[Zyuden Sentai Kyoryuger]]'' are also in the movie.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ameblo.jp/ryoryusei/ |title=最新情報 |publisher=Ameblo.jp |date=2014-02-09 |accessdate=2014-02-09}}</ref> [[Shun Sugata]] playing [[Kamen Rider ZX]] from the ''[[Birth of the 10th! Kamen Riders All Together!!]]'' TV special returns, also performing as Ambassador Darkness. [[Itsuji Itao]] of ''[[Kamen Rider The First]]'' plays Ren Aoi, Kamen Rider Fifteen, a main antagonist of the film.

==Video game==
A port of ''[[Kamen Rider: Climax Heroes]]'' titled {{nihongo4|''[[Kamen Rider: Climax Heroes#Climax Heroes W|Kamen Rider: Climax Heroes W]]''|仮面ライダー クライマックスヒーローズＷ（ダブル）|Kamen Raidā Kuraimakkusu Hīrōzu Daburu}} for the [[Wii]] was released on December 3, 2009.<ref>''Weekly Famitsu'', October 8, 2009</ref> It features Kamen Rider Double as a playable character and also features Dopants and other kaijin as characters in the game.

==Mini-dramas==
As part of the special features on the DVD releases, a series of short films are included called {{nihongo4|"Shotaro Hidari Hardboiled Delusion Diary"|左翔太郎ハードボイルド妄想日記|Hidari Shōtarō Hādoboirudo Mōsō Nikki}} in which Shotaro [[daydream]]s about what life would be like if he, Akiko, or Ryu acted differently. These feature a Dopant from the DVD volume in a completely different role than it had in the series proper. These are then followed by members of the cast discussing their favorite parts of the episodes included on the DVD volume.
